        }
    ],
    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Report Structure",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Executive Summary",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "Target Audience: C-level executives, management",
                        "Length: 1-2 pages",
                        "",
                        "Include:",
                        "- Engagement overview (scope, dates, methodology)",
                        "- Key findings summary (critical/high count)",
                        "- Overall risk assessment (Critical/High/Medium/Low)",
                        "- Top 3-5 recommendations",
                        "- Business impact statement",
                        "",
                        "Avoid:",
                        "- Technical jargon",
                        "- Detailed exploitation steps",
                        "- Overwhelming statistics"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Technical Findings",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "For each finding:",
                        "",
                        "1. Title",
                        "   - Clear, descriptive (e.g., \"SQL Injection in Login Form\")",
                        "",
                        "2. Severity Rating",
                        "   - Critical / High / Medium / Low / Informational",
                        "   - Include CVSS score if applicable",
                        "",
                        "3. Affected Asset(s)",
                        "   - URL, IP, hostname, application name",
                        "",
                        "4. Description",
                        "   - What the vulnerability is",
                        "   - Why it matters",
                        "   - Technical explanation",
                        "",
                        "5. Evidence/Proof of Concept",
                        "   - Screenshots",
                        "   - Request/response captures",
                        "   - Step-by-step reproduction",
                        "",
                        "6. Impact",
                        "   - What an attacker could achieve",
                        "   - Business implications",
                        "",
                        "7. Remediation",
                        "   - Specific fix recommendations",
                        "   - Code examples if applicable",
                        "   - Reference documentation",
                        "",
                        "8. References",
                        "   - CVE numbers",
                        "   - OWASP links",
                        "   - Vendor advisories"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Finding Template",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "```markdown"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "[SEVERITY] Finding Title",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Overview",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Brief description of the vulnerability."
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Affected Assets",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "https://app.target.com/login",
                        "192.168.1.100:8080"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Technical Details",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Detailed explanation of the vulnerability and how it was discovered."
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Proof of Concept",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Request:\n``http\nPOST /api/login HTTP/1.1\nHost: app.target.com\nContent-Type: application/json\n{\"username\":\"admin' OR '1'='1\",\"password\":\"test\"}\n`\nResponse:\n`http\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\n{\"status\":\"authenticated\",\"user\":\"admin\"}\n``"
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Impact",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "An attacker could bypass authentication and gain administrative access to the application, potentially leading to:\n- Data breach of customer information\n- Unauthorized financial transactions\n- Complete system compromise"
                },
                {
                    "heading": "CVSS Score",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "8.6 (High) - CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:N/A:N"
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Remediation",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "1. Use parameterized queries or prepared statements\n2. Implement input validation\n3. Apply principle of least privilege to database accounts\nSecure Code Example:\n``python\ncursor.execute(\"SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = %s\", (username,))\n``"
                },
                {
                    "heading": "References",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "- OWASP SQL Injection\n- CWE-89\n```"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Severity Ratings",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "CVSS 3.1",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "Base Score Range:",
                        "- 0.0         : None",
                        "- 0.1 - 3.9   : Low",
                        "- 4.0 - 6.9   : Medium",
                        "- 7.0 - 8.9   : High",
                        "- 9.0 - 10.0  : Critical",
                        "",
                        "Calculator: https://www.first.org/cvss/calculator/3.1",
                        "",
                        "Key Metrics:",
                        "- Attack Vector (AV): Network/Adjacent/Local/Physical",
                        "- Attack Complexity (AC): Low/High",
                        "- Privileges Required (PR): None/Low/High",
                        "- User Interaction (UI): None/Required",
                        "- Scope (S): Unchanged/Changed",
                        "- Confidentiality Impact (C): None/Low/High",
                        "- Integrity Impact (I): None/Low/High",
                        "- Availability Impact (A): None/Low/High"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Custom Severity Matrix",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "CRITICAL:",
                        "- Remote code execution",
                        "- Authentication bypass (admin)",
                        "- SQL injection with data exfiltration",
                        "- Unauthenticated access to sensitive data",
                        "",
                        "HIGH:",
                        "- Stored XSS affecting admins",
                        "- SSRF with internal access",
                        "- Privilege escalation",
                        "- Sensitive data exposure",
                        "",
                        "MEDIUM:",
                        "- Reflected XSS",
                        "- CSRF on sensitive functions",
                        "- Information disclosure",
                        "- Missing security headers",
                        "",
                        "LOW:",
                        "- Verbose error messages",
                        "- Directory listing",
                        "- Missing cookie flags",
                        "- Minor information disclosure",
                        "",
                        "INFORMATIONAL:",
                        "- Best practice recommendations",
                        "- Defense in depth suggestions",
                        "- No direct security impact"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Writing Tips",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Do's",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "✓ Be clear and concise",
                        "✓ Provide actionable recommendations",
                        "✓ Include evidence (screenshots, logs)",
                        "✓ Explain business impact",
                        "✓ Prioritize findings by risk",
                        "✓ Use consistent formatting",
                        "✓ Proofread for errors",
                        "✓ Test all PoC steps before including",
                        "✓ Redact sensitive data appropriately",
                        "✓ Include positive observations"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Don'ts",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "✗ Use inflammatory language",
                        "✗ Include personal opinions",
                        "✗ Provide incomplete findings",
                        "✗ Use unexplained jargon",
                        "✗ Include raw tool output without context",
                        "✗ Make assumptions without evidence",
                        "✗ Include out-of-scope findings",
                        "✗ Forget to mention failed attacks",
                        "✗ Leave credentials in screenshots",
                        "✗ Submit without review"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Report Templates",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Markdown Report",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "```markdown\n# Penetration Test Report"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "[Client Name]",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "[Date Range]",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "---\n# Document Control\n| Version | Date | Author | Changes |\n|---------|------|--------|---------|\n| 1.0 | 2024-01-15 | Tester | Initial draft |\n| 1.1 | 2024-01-17 | Reviewer | Final review |\n# Confidentiality Statement\nThis document contains confidential information...\n---\n# 1. Executive Summary\n[Summary content]\n# 2. Scope"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "2.1 In Scope",
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "app.target.com",
                "api.target.com",
                "192.168.1.0/24"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "2.2 Out of Scope",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "- Production database\n- Third-party integrations\n# 3. Methodology\n[Testing approach, tools used]\n# 4. Findings Summary\n| # | Finding | Severity | Status |\n|---|---------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | SQL Injection | Critical | Open |\n| 2 | XSS in Search | High | Open |\n| 3 | Missing HTTPS | Medium | Open |\n# 5. Detailed Findings\n[Individual findings using template above]\n# 6. Recommendations Summary\n[Prioritized remediation roadmap]\n# Appendix A: Tool Output\n[Raw scan results if needed]\n# Appendix B: Glossary\n[Technical terms explained]\n```"
        },
        {
            "heading": "Report Generation Tools",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Automated Tools",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Dradis - Collaboration and reporting",
